<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" author="Kieran O'Donnell" dateTime="2021-03-01T18:12:04" id="_ab14c165-91aa-46e9-9e1d-98e85ef2c3db" outputclass="ncc-clause" type="insert"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/></meta><sptc>6.3.7</sptc><title id="_364c4364-63d1-4d3e-8b13-8ad494670c87">Fixings and bearing for structural steel members</title><archive-num>New for 2022</archive-num><subclause id="_f4981192-88bc-492f-9d36-1b108ee58b09" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_92ff7351-f726-4aa2-9580-9c18b4b51a70">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>All bolts used in connections must be hot dip galvanised 300 g/m<sup id="_0b85496e-c22f-41b6-a21a-4f39e772c0f1">2</sup>.</p></subclause><subclause id="_eb18d971-068e-4571-a758-f118313625f7" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_119c9647-1d4d-4f49-8da5-feddfde0b652">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>Bearer connections must be fixed in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4775_0.10.0.xml#_9c812c2e-d918-47bf-9617-2658eb5d1616" id="_ccc9f84e-c521-4b96-9018-db616f124a5a" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 6.3.7a</xref>.</p></subclause><subclause id="_e75d57a5-8f6c-4a7f-a952-3814e499a781" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_e618731b-a85f-4bbb-9796-8d268829676b">SubClause</title><num>3</num><p>Joists, bearers and lintels must be restrained from lateral movement or twisting along their length by fixing rafters or joists to the top flange of the member so as to prevent the member from moving laterally.</p></subclause><subclause id="_b5b895cc-efdb-416d-aadd-6da8b2e61e12" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_9e16b5da-1497-444b-8af6-1cf9e0e1848e">SubClause</title><num>4</num><p>End supports for bearers and lintels must transfer loads to the footings and have a bearing distance as follows:</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_00d00cdc-efd4-4227-b772-0480f9348c9f">For single spans, the bearing distance must be not less than the width of the member.</li><li id="_316d88a5-9ca4-4dc9-a81b-4c216681f91a">For continuous spans, internal bearing must be not less than two times the width of the member.</li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_0c3ad9cd-6571-42d4-8dd8-bc2968fffba1" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_5fcb1cee-3d68-4f86-a5c3-1cbf06f1b85d">SubClause</title><num>5</num><p>Strutting beams must—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_11c16f4a-800a-41c8-b79e-95725bddd8ff">be supported and fixed in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4771_0.8.0.xml#_bf1eef55-cb7f-4558-9176-fde663c8967e" id="_9d46fdc5-4390-4bfb-a075-6e5a816b81a7" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 6.3.7b</xref>; and</li><li id="_194bf7cb-b2f0-47de-be21-1c694daad789">where ends are cut to suit roof pitch, be cut in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4777_0.12.0.xml#_b5edaef2-6cac-4c93-a491-91bb92d99c64" id="_56a32393-ed7e-462b-8d48-9f92c0d6c8a0" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 6.3.7c</xref>.</li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_0c059d48-5c83-4cd1-a443-201d21fa3eaa" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_7dabc50b-775e-4963-9246-5f757de6a244">SubClause</title><num>6</num><p>Lintels must be fixed in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4780_0.14.0.xml#_ad2c0b80-beec-4e7b-9f18-07469939e020" id="_07fefb93-cabe-4e9c-af3d-e038fbd84993" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figures 6.3.7d</xref>, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4783_0.13.0.xml#_ba2bd412-5efc-4062-bc73-4b98bcc4abc9" id="_f7eefad3-b3bd-4ed6-b472-a2a79f591f28" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">6.3.7e</xref>, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4785_0.7.0.xml#_725b76c3-9d61-48ff-b3f3-bb0a01a866cb" id="_ea2d180e-7410-4b8b-9f5f-60b1f0ed4009" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">6.3.7f</xref>, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4786_0.8.0.xml#_7fd51e0d-6d60-43c7-a018-df5f9ddecc65" id="_63045303-15eb-43d2-b2d5-1a3938325b9a" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">6.3.7g</xref> and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4787_0.6.0.xml#_4324f5cc-5308-49b8-9a0b-d6f1b0772fc8" id="_7f4943de-f24a-4f54-a904-69dd7896270f" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">6.3.7h</xref>.</p></subclause><image-reference author="Kieran O'Donnell" conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4775_0.10.0.xml" dateTime="2021-03-01T14:56:57" id="_9c812c2e-d918-47bf-9617-2658eb5d1616" type="insert"><num>6.3.7a</num><title id="_9955113c-4e44-42e0-8580-3238ca27a462">Bearer supporting a timber floor and non-loadbearing stud wall</title><image alt="Bearer supporting a timber floor and non-loadbearing stud wall" height="402" heightdpi="200" href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:6-3-7a-bearer-supporting-timber-floor-and-non-loadbearing-stud-wall.eps" longdescref="(a) example A. (b) example B." width="1200" widthdpi="200"><image height="402" heightdpi="200" href="C:\Users\bkiem\AppData\Roaming\Quark\XML Author\Temp\media1_c9a83167-e8cd-446f-a9a7-2e221df0b413.jpg" width="1200" widthdpi="200"/></image></image-reference><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4771_0.8.0.xml" id="_bf1eef55-cb7f-4558-9176-fde663c8967e"><num>6.3.7b</num><title id="_d243cd91-0d63-4a66-ba2f-bad37282387e">Strutting beam supporting roof and ceiling</title><image alt="Strutting beam supporting roof and ceiling" height="726" heightdpi="200" href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:6-3-7b-strutting-beam-supporting-roof-and-ceiling.eps" width="1200" widthdpi="200"><image height="726" heightdpi="200" href="C:\Users\bkiem\AppData\Roaming\Quark\XML Author\Temp\media1_a12078f1-14dc-4dce-b9da-b84e135debee.jpg" width="1200" widthdpi="200"/></image></image-reference><image-reference author="Kieran O'Donnell" conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4777_0.12.0.xml" dateTime="2021-03-01T14:58:00" id="_b5edaef2-6cac-4c93-a491-91bb92d99c64" type="insert"><num>6.3.7c</num><title id="_a80df296-bc64-4565-8938-430f0b1d54d8">End cuts to strutting beams</title><image href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:6-3-7c-end-cuts-to-strutting-beams.eps"><image _resize_="false" href="C:\Users\bkiem\AppData\Roaming\Quark\XML Author\Temp\media1_5fedfb6e-691f-4d39-94af-ee673d9c1c4b.tif" imagePlaceholder=""/></image><desc-note id="_2ce57556-9cad-4cd1-a5d2-237316f27354"><p>Strutting beam top plate to be tied down in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:6-3-4-strutting-beams.xml#_550c56f2-5dc5-4a8a-aa28-e1a8ab53a600" id="_220228e7-af2f-4397-9f6f-49cf8eeed009" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">6.3.4</xref>.</p></desc-note></image-reference><image-reference author="Kieran O'Donnell" conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4780_0.14.0.xml" dateTime="2021-03-01T14:58:19" id="_ad2c0b80-beec-4e7b-9f18-07469939e020" type="insert"><num>6.3.7d</num><title id="_e3ed75d8-9125-458c-9df7-394fe2b2e7a1">Lintels supporting roof, frames and timber floors</title><image href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:6-3-7d-lintels-supporting-roof-frames-and-timber-floors.eps"><image _resize_="false" href="C:\Users\bkiem\AppData\Roaming\Quark\XML Author\Temp\media1_e1c45e9a-536d-473c-9b6d-2361258611a0.tif" imagePlaceholder=""/></image></image-reference><image-reference author="Kieran O'Donnell" conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4783_0.13.0.xml" dateTime="2021-03-01T14:58:36" id="_ba2bd412-5efc-4062-bc73-4b98bcc4abc9" type="insert"><num>6.3.7e</num><title id="_37dc11c1-7647-48df-9e00-724eba2dc39d">Lintels supporting roof, frames and timber floors — sections</title><image href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:6-3-7e-lintels-supporting-roof-frames-and-timber-floors-section.eps"><image _resize_="false" href="C:\Users\bkiem\AppData\Roaming\Quark\XML Author\Temp\media1_b3b0df3f-3f34-4809-a5f1-d50fb41177ca.tif" imagePlaceholder=""/></image></image-reference><image-reference author="Kieran O'Donnell" conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4785_0.7.0.xml" dateTime="2021-03-01T14:58:51" id="_725b76c3-9d61-48ff-b3f3-bb0a01a866cb" type="insert"><num>6.3.7f</num><title id="_edbafcb3-1097-4218-91cb-b4d8325eef27">Typical universal beam to column connection detail</title><image alt="Typical universal beam to column connection detail" height="545" heightdpi="200" href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:6-3-7f-typical-universal-beam-to-column-connection-detail.eps" width="1200" widthdpi="200"><image height="545" heightdpi="200" href="C:\Users\bkiem\AppData\Roaming\Quark\XML Author\Temp\media1_f64204c1-29c7-48e7-8ac7-1217e98407e6.jpg" width="1200" widthdpi="200"/></image><desc-note id="_945a7537-c531-4bf1-8f55-aa7abd2a65e1"><ol outputclass="numbered"><li id="_6d54b381-c09d-4866-84d0-2aebe1297249">8 mm steel plates to be welded to the top and bottom of the column using 5 mm fillet welds.</li><li id="_ecad8c0a-88ca-4829-8da8-d905dcb22bad">Plate width must be the greater of the column width or the beam width.</li><li id="_d60ca1f3-b323-43a1-a03a-e5d5e0218595">Plate length must be such that there is not less than 40 mm from the centreline of the bolts to the ends.</li><li id="_e4727162-baef-447b-a831-db566ce218b8">All bolting between structural steel members must be not less than 2 M12 4.6/S.</li></ol></desc-note></image-reference><image-reference author="Kieran O'Donnell" conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4786_0.8.0.xml" dateTime="2021-03-01T14:59:10" id="_7fd51e0d-6d60-43c7-a018-df5f9ddecc65" type="insert"><num>6.3.7g</num><title id="_84247e34-93e7-4e57-aa60-92aac3406f8b">Typical PFC and RHS beam to column connection detail</title><image alt="Typical PFC and RHS beam to column connection detail" height="517" heightdpi="200" href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:6-3-7g-typical-PFC-and-RHS-beam-to-column-connection-detail.eps" width="1200" widthdpi="200"><image height="517" heightdpi="200" href="C:\Users\bkiem\AppData\Roaming\Quark\XML Author\Temp\media1_4c5c9ae8-1d6e-49d3-81f7-d23cd470aedc.jpg" width="1200" widthdpi="200"/></image></image-reference><image-reference author="Kieran O'Donnell" conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4787_0.6.0.xml" dateTime="2021-03-01T14:59:31" id="_4324f5cc-5308-49b8-9a0b-d6f1b0772fc8" type="insert"><num>6.3.7h</num><title id="_dee1fda5-8722-49dc-9bd6-13db1c8ebef6">Typical column base plate detail</title><image alt="Typical column base plate detail" height="1800" heightdpi="200" href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:6-3-7h-typical-column-base-plate-detail.eps" width="754" widthdpi="200"><image height="1800" heightdpi="200" href="C:\Users\bkiem\AppData\Roaming\Quark\XML Author\Temp\media1_41a8cff2-679f-4b0a-8c1d-c923ac5cb334.jpg" width="754" widthdpi="200"/></image><desc-note id="_84029402-fdac-4d82-b5b6-7e4bb6051567" title="Figure Notes"><p>Fixing of the column base plate to the slab must be not less than 2 M12 4.6/S post-installed mechanical anchors.</p></desc-note></image-reference><callout id="_cbc893a1-865b-4a7c-8938-ebc5d059d219"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>The ends of bearers and lintels must be sufficiently supported to ensure structural loads are transferred to the footing system. The amount of horizontal bearing (measured in millimetres) required on the vertical supports will depend on the type of span of the bearer or lintel. For single spans, the amount of horizontal bearing is to be equal to or greater than the width of the bearer or lintel. For continuous spans it is to be twice the width of the bearer or lintel.</p><p>For bearing distance, see 6.3.7(4)(a) and (b).</p><p><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4788_0.6.0.xml#_f63d500d-3dbe-4274-984c-55ac796ebf2b" id="_10f06d1c-fd11-4848-873e-84082f751943" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Explanatory Figure 6.3.7</xref> depicts an example of a 200 PFC bearer or lintel supporting floor or roof loads over a single span.</p><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4788_0.6.0.xml" id="_f63d500d-3dbe-4274-984c-55ac796ebf2b"><num>6.3.7 (explanatory)</num><title id="_73c95a29-c763-4107-bea7-89edb891d042">Example of a 200 PFC bearer or lintel supporting floor or roof loads over a single span</title><image alt="Example of a 200 PFC bearer or lintel supporting floor or roof loads over a single span" height="884" heightdpi="200" href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:6-3-7-explanatory-example-200-PFC-bearer-or-lintel-supporting-floor-or-roof-loads-over-single-span.eps" width="1144" widthdpi="200"><image height="884" heightdpi="200" href="C:\Users\bkiem\AppData\Roaming\Quark\XML Author\Temp\media1_5abb861f-85d9-4561-819d-d335697e38a6.jpg" width="1144" widthdpi="200"/></image></image-reference></callout></clause>